Name: Banded Broadbill
Breeding Range-Subregion: Southeast Asia to Java and Borneo

Name: Blue-throated Bee-eater
Breeding Range-Subregion: s China to Java and Philippines

Name: Buff-vented Bulbul
Breeding Range-Subregion: se Myanmar, s Thailand, Malay Peninsula, Sumatra and nearby islands
Comment: Species epithet crypta Oberholser, 1918 replaces olivacea Blyth, 1844 which is permanently invalid. See Dickinson & Christidis 2014

Name: Chestnut-necklaced Partridge
Comment: Change  English name of Arborophila charltonii from Scaly-breasted Partridge to Chestnut-necklaced Partridge to conform to current usage for charltoni sensu stricto

Name: Crested Jay
Comment: Platylophus is probably a shrike, not a jay (Jønsson et al. 2008b)

Name: Cricket Frog
Breeding Range-Subregion: Philippines, Indonesia, Malaysia, Thailaind, India (Nicobar Island)

Name: Dark-throated Oriole
Breeding Range-Subregion: Southeast Asia through Borneo and Philippines

Name: Four-lined Tree Frog
Breeding Range-Subregion: India, South East Asia, Nepal, Japan (Ryukyus)

Name: Golden-bellied Gerygone
Breeding Range-Subregion: Malay Peninsula, Sundas, Philippines, also Sulawesi

Name: Olive-winged Bulbul
Breeding Range-Subregion: s Myanmar and s Thailand, peninsular Malaysia, Greater Sundas

Name: Oriental Dwarf Kingfisher
Comment: Rufous-backed morphs sometimes treated as separate species C. rufidorsa (King 1997, Rasmussen & Anderton 2005, Lim et al. 2010) suggest past episodes of secondary contact and introgression. Revisit status of rufidorsa.

Name: Pacific Swallow
Breeding Range-Subregion: se Asia to New Guinea and Society Islands

Name: Rufous-tailed Shama
Breeding Range-Subregion: extreme s Thailand, Malaysia, Sumatra, Borneo

Name: Scarlet Minivet
Comment: Pericrocotus speciosus is split from P. flammeus (Rasmussen & Anderton 2005).

Name: Slender-billed Crow
Breeding Range-Subregion: Malaysia to Borneo, Philippines, also Sulawesi

Name: Square-tailed Drongo Cuckoo
Breeding Range-Subregion: nw Himalayas to se China, south to s Thailand, Malaysia, Greater Sundas and Palawan
Comment: Change  English name of Surniculus lugubris to Square-tailed Drongo-Cuckoo with splits of S. dicruroides and D. musschenbroeki. Subspecific taxonomy, nomenclature and ranges of this species and Fork-tailed Drongo-Cuckoo are tentative and based primarily on  Payne, 2005 modified by Rasmussen & Anderton, 2005. For alternate treatments see Erritzøe et al, 2012  and Dickinson & Remsen, 2013.

Name: Van Hasselt's Sunbird
Breeding Range-Subregion: ne India to Southeast Asia and Greater Sundas

Name: Wreathed Hornbill
Breeding Range-Subregion: ne India to Borneo and Java
